Step 1: Install VS Code

Step 2: Download MSYS2 & Install - Link: https://www.msys2.org/

Step 3: After installing, Terminal will open and type: "pacman -Syu". Then press Y. This will update the whole package.

Step 4: Open "MSYS UCRT64" And Type: pacman -Su.

Step 5: For installing C++ Compiler Run Command: 
64bit - "pacman -S --needed base-devel mingw-w64-ucrt-x86\_64-toolchain"
32bit - "pacman -S --needed base-devel mingw-w64-i686-toolchain"

Step 6: Press Return Key. And type Y. This will install Compiler.

Step 7: Then go to Search Bar, Type "Edit the System Environment Variable" \& Open It, Select "Environment Variables".

Step 8: Select Path > Edit > New > Paste The Folder Bin Where Msys was installed "C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin". Hit OK.

Step 9: Open VS Code, Install VS Code Extension. (C++ From Microsoft).

Step 10: Then Create A CPP File and Run Code. Make sure to select g++.

**For F5 Run --> Select gdb/lldb.**
